ZH: 政治家不应该煽动人民的情绪。
EN: Politicians should not incite the emotions of the people.

ZH: 这位演讲者煽动了听众的愤怒。
EN: The speaker incited anger among the audience.

ZH: 煽动他人的仇恨是不道德的行为。
EN: Inciting hatred in others is unethical behavior.

ZH: 这篇文章试图煽动读者的情绪。
EN: This article attempts to incite the emotions of the readers.

ZH: 不要被别人煽动起来。
EN: Do not let others incite you.

ZH: 他煽动了抗议者继续游行。
EN: He incited the protesters to continue marching.

ZH: 这种行为可能会煽动暴力事件。
EN: Such behavior could incite violence.

ZH: 我们不能容忍任何形式的煽动。
EN: We cannot tolerate any form of incitement.

ZH: 这些广告试图煽动年轻人购买他们的产品。
EN: These ads try to incite young people to buy their products.

ZH: 煽动种族仇恨是一种严重的罪行。
EN: Inciting racial hatred is a serious crime.

ZH: 他被指控煽动邮寄恐吓信。
EN: He was accused of inciting the mailing of threatening letters.

ZH: 他的言论煽动了一场反政府示威。
EN: His remarks incited a demonstration against the government.

ZH: 这些言论试图煽动敌对国家之间的紧张关系。
EN: These remarks attempt to incite tension between hostile nations.

ZH: 我们绝不支持任何形式的煽动。
EN: We do not support any form of incitement.

ZH: 这种宣传画煽动民众参加纪念活动。
EN: This propaganda poster incites the public to join in the commemoration event.

ZH: 煽动仇恨会导致社会分裂。
EN: Inciting hatred can lead to social division.

ZH: 这部电影被指责煽动暴力行为。
EN: This movie was criticized for inciting violence.

ZH: 这个团体试图煽动人们反对政府政策。
EN: This group is trying to incite people to oppose government policies.

ZH: 煽动年轻人去参加激进组织是危险的。
EN: Inciting young people to join radical organizations is dangerous.

ZH: 反动势力一直在煽动民众进行暴力抗议。
EN: Reactionary forces have been inciting the people to engage in violent protests.
